The paper deals with the problem of securing a multicast network against a wiretapper, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). It also discusses the use of network coding techniques, which is a topic in both IT and distributed systems (DS). The paper also addresses the issue of network security, which falls under the category of computer security (CR) and system and information theory (SI).
